SIMPLE: nonexempt
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nonexempt
<hw>nonexempt</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not exempt; subject
to (some specified) rule. Opposite of <ant>exempt</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>liable to(predicate)</stype>; <stype>subject, subject
to(predicate)</stype>]⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(U. S. Labor
Law)</fld> <def>Not exempt from the provisions of the fair labor
practices act; -- a term applied mostly to persons who are hourly
employees, who are required by law to be treated in certain ways. Many
salaried and management personnel are not covered by the law and are
therefore <contr>exempt</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonexistence</ent>⟦br⟧
